    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "list",
    "sub_type": "text",
    "list_items": [
      "GGMs provides structural information: $\\Omega _ { i j } = 0$ implies conditional independenceoffeatures $i$ and $j$ givenall remaining features ",
      "Maximum likelihood estimate of $\\Omega$ is not sparse and for $d > n$ is not unique penalized likelihood to encourage sparse $\\Omega$ $\\begin{array} { r } { \\operatorname * { a r g m a x } _ { \\Omega \\sim 0 } \\{ \\log \\operatorname* { d e t } \\Omega - \\operatorname { T r } ( \\frac { 1 } { n } S \\Omega ) - \\lambda \\| \\Omega \\| _ { 0 } \\} } \\end{array}$ "
    ],
    "bbox": [
      26,
      290,
      318,
      413
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Intractable because the objective is highly non-convex ",
    "bbox": [
      36,
      421,
      239,
      439
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "· Graphical Lasso: use convex relaxation $\\| \\Omega \\| _ { 0 } \\longrightarrow \\| \\Omega \\| _ { 1 }$ ",
    "bbox": [
      26,
      458,
      257,
      479
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Benefits ",
    "text_level": 1,
    "bbox": [
      27,
      502,
      68,
      518
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "$\\clubsuit$ Solution path: frequentist approach provides solutions as a function of $\\lambda$ ",
    "bbox": [
      27,
      521,
      307,
      538
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Limitations ",
    "text_level": 1,
    "bbox": [
      27,
      556,
      78,
      571
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "list",
    "sub_type": "text",
    "list_items": [
      "$\\clubsuit$ Over-shrinking: $l _ { 1 }$ norm causes well-known over-shrinking of features ",
      "$\\clubsuit$ No credibility interval "
    ],
    "bbox": [
      27,
      576,
      297,
      609
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Bayesian Graphical Lasso ",
    "text_level": 1,
    "bbox": [
      90,
      658,
      257,
      681
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "list",
    "sub_type": "text",
    "list_items": [
      "·Bayesian approach: $p ( \\Omega | S , \\lambda ) \\propto p ( S | \\Omega ) \\ p ( \\Omega | \\lambda )$ ",
      "· Encourage sparsity with double exponential prior (DE) "
    ],
    "bbox": [
      31,
      691,
      240,
      739
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\np (S | \\Omega) \\propto \\mathcal {W} _ {d} (n, \\Omega^ {- 1})\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      44,
      746,
      131,
      767
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "equation",
    "text": "$$\np (\\Omega | \\lambda) \\propto \\mathcal {W} _ {d} (d + 1, \\lambda 1 _ {d}) \\prod_ {i <   j} \\mathrm {D E} (\\omega_ {i j} | \\lambda) I [ \\Omega \\succ 0 ]\n$$",
    "text_format": "latex",
    "bbox": [
      44,
      767,
      235,
      804
    ],
    "page_idx": 0,
    "img_path": ""
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "·Recovers the $l _ { 1 }$ norm penalized likelihood solution in the MAP limit ",
    "bbox": [
      33,
      805,
      287,
      821
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Benefits ",
    "text_level": 1,
    "bbox": [
      26,
      840,
      65,
      855
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "$\\clubsuit$ Credibility interval: canbe computed within Bayesian framework ",
    "bbox": [
      26,
      859,
      279,
      875
    ],
    "page_idx": 0
  },
  {
    "type": "text",
    "text": "Limitations ",
